The paper deals with integer programming and polytopes, which are topics related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of Gaussian distributions and the study of the radius of the largest inscribed ball suggest information theory (cs.IT) and computational geometry (cs.CG) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the mention of a randomized polynomial-time algorithm suggests numerical analysis (cs.NA) as a possible sub-category.
